From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: winex11.drv: zero-copy AHB GPU present over the X-server side-channel

Phase 3 of the GPU X-server upgrade. Replaces the per-frame GPU->CPU
readback in vstpoc_on_image (patch 0032's AImage_getPlaneData + XPutImage)
with a zero-copy path: when VSTPOC_AHB_PRESENT=1, ship each rendered frame's
AHardwareBuffer (the AImageReader's images are already AHB-backed) + its
acquire-fence over a private AF_UNIX side-channel to the in-process X server,
which imports it as an EGLImage and composites it directly. No CPU copy.

- Connect the abstract socket "guitarrack-ahb-<display>" at surface create
  (display parsed from DISPLAY); connect failure falls back to readback.
- Per frame: REGISTER (buffer_count=1) + the AHB handle via SCM_RIGHTS
  (AHardwareBuffer_sendHandleToUnixSocket from libandroid.so) + PRESENT with
  the acquire-fence. HOLD the AImage 1-deep so DXVK can't reuse a buffer the
  server is still sampling; the previous held image returns to the pool.
- AImageReader usage gains GPU_SAMPLED_IMAGE (0x303) so Adreno-EGL can sample
  it; maxImages 4->6 for hold headroom. AhbChannelProtocol.h is vendored from
  vsthost_lib/src/main/cpp/x11/ (POSIX sockets only, byte-identical wire).

Default-off (env-gated); existing plugins keep the readback path. Slots after
patch 0032 (the AImageReader present). Device-validated: BIAS FX 2 editor
renders pixel-correct via zero-copy on OnePlus 12 / Adreno 750.

